Class QueryParams

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<K,V>
        • java.util.LinkedHashMap<String,List<String>>
          • nl.naturalis.nda.search.QueryParams
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Map<String,List<String>>

    public class QueryParams
extends LinkedHashMap<String,List<String>>
    A class capturing the input for an ElasticSearch query. This class mimicks and is functionally equivalent to the javax.ws.rs.core.MultiValuedMap interface within the JAX-RS framework. When passing URL query parameters in to DAOs, the REST resource classes copy them from a MultiValuedMap to a QueryParams object. This way the DAO project can avoid an awkward dependency on the JAX-RS framework.
    Author:
    ayco_holleman

    • Constructor Detail

      • QueryParams

        public QueryParams(Map<?,?> map)
        Instantiate a QueryParams instance from another map. Although the constructor argument does not specify any concrete type of Map, it really is presumed to be one of:
        1. javax.ws.rs.core.MultiValuedMap<String,String>
        2. Map<String,List<String>>
        3. Map<String,String>
        In the latter case the values are converted to a List<String>>. ClassCastExceptions for either keys or values are not trapped; the caller must make sure the constructor argument has the appropriate type arguments.
        Parameters:
        map - The Map to convert to a QueryParams object.
        See Also:
        addParams(Map)
